16 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 49 O.S. 2021, Section 1, is
17 amended to read as follows:
18 Section 1. The Secretary of State shall appoint and commission
19 in this state notaries public, who shall hold their office for four
20 (4) years. An applicant for a notary commission shall be eighteen
21 (18) years of age or older, a citizen of the United States, and
22 employed within this state or a legal resident of this state. A
23 national criminal history record check, as defined in Section 150.9
24 of Title 74 of the Oklahoma Statutes, shall be conducted
