5 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 49 O.S. 2021, Section 2, is
6 amended to read as follows:
7 Section 2. A. Before entering upon the duties of his or her
8 office and not more than sixty (60) days after issuance of a notary
9 commission, every notary public so appointed and commissioned shall
10 file in the office of the Secretary of State, the notary’s oath of
11 office, the notary’s loyalty oath, the notary’s official signature,
12 an impression of the notary’s official seal, and a good and
13 sufficient bond to the State of Oklahoma, in the sum of One Thousand
14 Dollars ($1,000.00) Ten Thousand Dollars ($10,000.00), to be
15 approved by the Secretary of State, conditioned for the faithful
16 performance of the duties of the notary’s office.
17 B. The bond required by subsection A of this section shall be
18 signed by:
19 1. An insurance agent licensed by the State of Oklahoma;
20 2. An attorney-in-fact on behalf of an insurance company with a
21 power of attorney attached; or
22 3. One or more individual sureties who are property owners in
23 the county of residence of the notary, or if a nonresident, the
24 county of employment of the notary.
